snippet.description:

Step into Jethalal‚Äôs world with Gada Electronics!  Manage the shop, tackle quirky customers, and experience nonstop TMKOC-style fun.

#GadaElectronics #TMKOCGame

Click here to watch your favourite videos from Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Episode 4440: Toota Popatlal Ka Dil
------------------------------------------------------------
Popatlal learns the shocking truth from the caretaker that Chakori is indeed a ghost. How will he cope with this unexpected and frightening discovery?

Show Name ‚Äì Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah
Star Cast ‚Äì  Dilip Joshi, Disha Vakani, Amit Bhatt, Nitish Bhaluni
Episodes No - Ep 4440 | 3 July 2025

#TaarakMehtaKaOoltahChashmah #‡§§‡§æ‡§∞‡§ï‡§Æ‡•á‡§π‡§§‡§æ‡§ï‡§æ‡§â‡§≤‡•ç‡§ü‡§æ‡§ö‡§∂‡•ç‡§Æ‡§æ #sab #Latest #New #TaarakMehtaKaOoltahChashmah2025 #tmkocfunnyepisodes #hindicomedy #comedyvideo #16yearsoftmkoc  #4000episodes

About the show: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. Some love stories aren't just written in hearts‚Äîthey're carved through pain, sacrifice, and fire. Enter the world of Sher, where two souls‚ÄîSher Zaman and Fajar‚Äîdare to love beyond the lines drawn by generations of hate.

Danish Taimoor breathes life into Sher Zaman, a man raised with command in his veins‚Äîfierce, proud, and built to lead.
Sarah Khan shines as Fajar, a gentle heart swept into the storm of a family feud, trying to hold on to love and light in a world clouded by old grudges.

Their paths were never meant to cross. But love‚Ä¶ had other plans.

Sher is a gripping Pakistani drama packed with raw emotions, intense rivalries, and deep-rooted traditions.
From kidnappings and secret alliances to broken promises and forbidden love, every episode leaves you wanting more.

Parwarish Episode 25 | Digitally Presented by Surf Excel , Vince Care, Mothercare &  VGOTEL | Aina Asif | Samar Jafri | Reham Rafiq | 1st JULY 2025 | ARY Digital Drama 

PARWARISH ‚Äì The most-watched Pakistani drama of the season, Parwarish is a gripping tale of generational conflict, where love becomes control and independence feels like rebellion. As parents hold tight to cultural traditions and children chase dreams of freedom, misunderstandings shake the very foundation of the family. It‚Äôs a powerful reflection of the emotional battles playing out in households across Pakistan today.


Samar Jafri as Wali Jahangir:
Wali, the eldest son of Jahangir, is the emotional heart of Parwarish. Handsome, intelligent, and kind-hearted, Wali was raised in the freedom of America. He dreams of becoming a musician, but his father‚Äôs disapproval casts a long shadow. Now back in Pakistan, Wali must navigate a world where parental expectations and personal dreams collide, sparking the drama‚Äôs central conflict.

Aina Asif as Maya:
Maya, a bright and determined girl from a conservative, middle-class family, is ready to take on the world. Beautiful and self-assured, she aspires to become a doctor‚Äîa path her family supports only conditionally. Caught between love, ambition, and tradition, Maya embodies the struggle of many young women in today‚Äôs society.

It‚Äôs a powerful reflection of the emotional battles playing out in households across Pakistan today.


Samar Jafri as Wali Jahangir:
Wali, the eldest son of Jahangir, is the emotional heart of Parwarish. Handsome, intelligent, and kind-hearted, Wali was raised in the freedom of America. He dreams of becoming a musician, but his father‚Äôs disapproval casts a long shadow. Now back in Pakistan, Wali must navigate a world where parental expectations and personal dreams collide, sparking the drama‚Äôs central conflict.

Aina Asif as Maya:
Maya, a bright and determined girl from a conservative, middle-class family, is ready to take on the world. Beautiful and self-assured, she aspires to become a doctor‚Äîa path her family supports only conditionally. Caught between love, ambition, and tradition, Maya embodies the struggle of many young women in today‚Äôs society.

snippet.title: Charity or Showbiz? | Dreamz Unlimited
snippet.description:
In this short video, we reflect on a growing concern within our churches,  are we truly giving from the heart, or are we more concerned about our name being announced in public? Too often, people give generously to the church just to gain recognition, while neglecting genuine needs like community development or council initiatives that benefit everyone.

Let‚Äôs pause and ask ourselves: Is our giving rooted in love, faith, and responsibility ‚Äî or is it driven by pride and empty tradition? True giving is quiet, sincere, and purposeful.

Welcome back to RelationShit Advice. A show where I (Raunaq Rajani) call 3 of my funny friends each episode, and we give the absolute worst relationship advice to people who've emailed us with their problems. snippet.description:
Step into Jethalal‚Äôs world with Gada Electronics!  Manage the shop, tackle quirky customers, and experience nonstop TMKOC-style fun. Are you ready for the challenge? 

 Play now: https://gadaelectronics.page.link/dhgB  #GadaElectronics #TMKOCGame

Click here to watch your favourite videos from Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. snippet.title: The Coldest Village on Earth (I got facial paralysis, couldn't speak) -71¬∞C, -96¬∞F
snippet.description:
Use the coupon code RUHI29 to buy the MyHeritage DNA kit for only $29/‚Ç¨29/¬£29 https://bit.ly/RuhiCenet_MH or start your family tree with a 14-day free trial.

Here is my friend's video:
Journey to the World's Coldest Village: Oymyakon at -71¬∞C https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w6fyb46Z-SM
Don't forget to check out "The Ulengovs" channel: https://www.youtube.com/@TheUlengovs

Thanks to MyHeritage for sponsoring this video. (There is a brand integration in this video) (Bu videoda marka entegrasyonu, √ºr√ºn reklamƒ± vardƒ±r)

Imagine a village where temperatures drop as low as -71¬∞C, -96¬∞F. Here, spending just a few extra minutes outside can lead to frostbite, the loss of a limb, or even end of life.

I‚Äôm in the coldest inhabited place on Earth, at the coldest time of the year. This is Oymyakon. Just to stay alive, I‚Äôm wearing more than 20 layers of clothing, weighing nearly 14 kilos. Stepping outside from a warm 30¬∞C home means facing a temperature drop of over 100 degrees. That‚Äôs why I‚Äôm also wearing gloves, boots, pants, and a coat, all made from reindeer fur. And even that‚Äôs not enough. And now, I‚Äôm about to show you what life is like when simply going outside becomes a battle for survival.

The cold doesn't just affect people and wild animals. It stops everything from functioning.  Phones don‚Äôt work properly and often shut down. Cars left outside freeze in just a few hours. Since the ground is always frozen, no fruits or vegetables can grow here.

We boarded a plane in Moscow, flying east for seven hours to Yakutsk. From there, we covered an 18 hour, 900 kilometer road trip. When we stepped out of the car, it felt like we were on another planet. The hairs in our nose were frozen, and we felt them prick with every breath. The dry air makes us cough uncontrollably.  

Oymyakon is home to around 800 people, spread across 1.5 square kilometers. Seeing anyone else outside is almost impossible, the village feels like it has been abandoned.

Our team that worked on this project ‚ñ∫ https://docs.google.com/document/d/1vDYIkyfFR1fayrUZOsA80xEN3X-nYhU003F1FewGCy8/edit?usp=sharing

Subscribe ‚ñ∫ https://goo.gl/MKi8tn
"Rediscovery" Series ‚ñ∫ https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL40Eh9f0PRRXcCkyKxrtRvE3tbmcKYvHr

Visiting the Fattest, Most Cigarette-Addicted and Least Visited Country üá≥üá∑ ‚ñ∫ https://youtu.be/eUJgq9HerDQ
Visiting the World's Hottest Place (70¬∞C, 159¬∞F) LUT DESERT ‚ñ∫ https://youtu.be/NhyDkHaUC8U
Visiting the World‚Äôs Most Da–øge–≥ous Road: ‚ÄúKarakoram D‚ÑÆath Road‚Äù (There are casuaIti‚ÑÆs!) ‚ñ∫ https://youtu.be/FryCzL17YRs
Visiting the MOST AIR POLLUTED CITY in the World (Dust Hell) ‚ñ∫ https://youtu.be/zC4saZg6sG0
Visiting the COLDEST CITY in the World (-71¬∞C, -96¬∞F) YAKUTSK / YAKUTIA ‚ñ∫ https://youtu.be/Fz4ZMLsPzqM
8 Crazy Experiments at -55¬∞C, -67¬∞F (The coldest city in the World: Yakutsk) ‚ñ∫ https://youtu.be/ExoOL2lwlWE
World's Poorest Country "Burundi" (I can‚Äôt forget the things I saw) ‚ñ∫ https://youtu.be/n0gFsHf9cIw

My name is Ruhi √áenet, I'm an independent documentary maker. I go to unique places or meet unique people and investigate or analyze them with a unique approach. My motto is "curiosity is the best guide". Join me, let's learn something different...

it.title: Il Villaggio Pi√π Freddo al Mondo (Ho avuto una paralisi facciale) -71¬∞C
it.description:
Usa il codice coupon RUHI29 per acquistare il kit DNA MyHeritage a soli $29/‚Ç¨29/¬£29 https://bit.ly/RuhiCenet_MH oppure inizia il tuo albero genealogico con una prova gratuita di 14 giorni.

Non dimenticare di dare un'occhiata al canale "The Ulengovs": https://www.youtube.com/@TheUlengovs

Immaginate un villaggio dove le temperature scendono fino a -71 ¬∞C, -96 ¬∞F. Qui, trascorrere solo pochi minuti in pi√π all'aperto pu√≤ portare a congelamenti, alla perdita di un arto o persino alla fine della vita.

Mi trovo nel luogo abitato pi√π freddo della Terra, nel periodo pi√π freddo dell'anno. Questa √® Oymyakon. Solo per sopravvivere, indosso pi√π di 20 strati di vestiti, per un peso di quasi 14 chili. Uscire da una casa calda a 30 ¬∞C significa affrontare un calo di temperatura di oltre 38 gradi. Ecco perch√© indosso anche guanti, stivali, pantaloni e un cappotto, tutti di pelliccia di renna. E anche questo non basta. E ora sto per mostrarvi com'√® la vita quando semplicemente uscire diventa una lotta per la sopravvivenza.

Il freddo non colpisce solo le persone e gli animali selvatici. Impedisce a tutto di funzionare. I telefoni non funzionano correttamente e spesso si spengono. Le auto lasciate fuori si congelano in poche ore. Dato che il terreno √® sempre ghiacciato, qui non cresce n√© frutta n√© verdura.

Siamo saliti su un aereo a Mosca, volando verso est per sette ore fino a Yakutsk. Da l√¨, abbiamo percorso 900 chilometri in auto per 18 ore. Quando siamo scesi dall'auto, ci siamo sentiti come su un altro pianeta. I peli del naso erano congelati e li sentivamo pungere a ogni respiro. L'aria secca ci fa tossire in modo incontrollabile.

Oymyakon ospita circa 800 persone, distribuite su 1,5 chilometri quadrati. Vedere qualcun altro all'esterno √® quasi impossibile, il villaggio sembra abbandonato.

en.title: The Coldest Village on Earth (I got facial paralysis, couldn't speak) -71¬∞C, -96¬∞F
en.description:
Use the coupon code RUHI29 to buy the MyHeritage DNA kit for only $29/‚Ç¨29/¬£29 https://bit.ly/RuhiCenet_MH or start your family tree with a 14-day free trial.

Here is my friend's video:
Journey to the World's Coldest Village: Oymyakon at -71¬∞C https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w6fyb46Z-SM
Don't forget to check out "The Ulengovs" channel: https://www.youtube.com/@TheUlengovs

Thanks to MyHeritage for sponsoring this video. (There is a brand integration in this video) (Bu videoda marka entegrasyonu, √ºr√ºn reklamƒ± vardƒ±r)

Imagine a village where temperatures drop as low as -71¬∞C, -96¬∞F. Here, spending just a few extra minutes outside can lead to frostbite, the loss of a limb, or even end of life.

I‚Äôm in the coldest inhabited place on Earth, at the coldest time of the year. This is Oymyakon. Just to stay alive, I‚Äôm wearing more than 20 layers of clothing, weighing nearly 14 kilos. Stepping outside from a warm 30¬∞C home means facing a temperature drop of over 100 degrees. That‚Äôs why I‚Äôm also wearing gloves, boots, pants, and a coat, all made from reindeer fur. And even that‚Äôs not enough. And now, I‚Äôm about to show you what life is like when simply going outside becomes a battle for survival.

The cold doesn't just affect people and wild animals. It stops everything from functioning.  Phones don‚Äôt work properly and often shut down. Cars left outside freeze in just a few hours. Since the ground is always frozen, no fruits or vegetables can grow here.

We boarded a plane in Moscow, flying east for seven hours to Yakutsk. From there, we covered an 18 hour, 900 kilometer road trip. When we stepped out of the car, it felt like we were on another planet. The hairs in our nose were frozen, and we felt them prick with every breath. The dry air makes us cough uncontrollably.  

Oymyakon is home to around 800 people, spread across 1.5 square kilometers. Seeing anyone else outside is almost impossible, the village feels like it has been abandoned.

Saya berada di tempat berpenghuni terdingin di Bumi, pada waktu terdingin dalam setahun. Ini adalah Oymyakon. Agar tetap hidup, saya mengenakan lebih dari 20 lapis pakaian, yang beratnya hampir 14 kilogram. Saat kami keluar dari mobil, rasanya seperti berada di planet lain. Bulu hidung kami membeku, dan kami merasakannya menusuk setiap kali bernapas. Udara kering membuat kami batuk-batuk tak terkendali.

Oymyakon adalah rumah bagi sekitar 800 orang, tersebar di wilayah seluas 1,5 kilometer persegi. Hampir mustahil untuk melihat orang lain di luar, desa itu terasa seperti telah ditinggalkan.

Stell dir ein Dorf vor, in dem die Temperaturen auf bis zu -71 ¬∞C (-96 ¬∞F) fallen. Schon ein paar zus√§tzliche Minuten im Freien k√∂nnen zu Erfrierungen, dem Verlust eines K√∂rperteils oder sogar zum Tod f√ºhren.

Ich befinde mich am k√§ltesten bewohnten Ort der Erde, zur k√§ltesten Jahreszeit. Das ist Oimjakon. Um am Leben zu bleiben, trage ich mehr als 20 Schichten Kleidung und wiege fast 14 Kilo. Wenn ich mein 30 ¬∞C warmes Zuhause verlasse, muss ich mit einem Temperaturabfall von √ºber 38 Grad rechnen. Deshalb trage ich auch Handschuhe, Stiefel, Hosen und einen Mantel ‚Äì alles aus Rentierfell. Und selbst das reicht nicht. Und jetzt zeige ich euch, wie das Leben aussieht, wenn schon der blo√üe Aufenthalt im Freien zum √úberlebenskampf wird.

Die K√§lte setzt nicht nur Menschen und Wildtieren zu. Sie legt alles lahm. Telefone funktionieren nicht richtig und fallen oft aus. Autos, die drau√üen stehen, frieren innerhalb weniger Stunden ein. Da der Boden immer gefroren ist, kann hier weder Obst noch Gem√ºse wachsen.

Die trockene Luft lie√ü uns unkontrolliert husten.

Oimjakon ist die Heimat von rund 800 Menschen, verteilt auf 1,5 Quadratkilometern. Drau√üen ist es fast unm√∂glich, jemanden zu sehen, das Dorf wirkt verlassen.

How to make tikhat mitachya purya | Ashadh Special Tikhat purya Recipe | How to make Ashadh special kapanya dhapate recipe
For the paste:To prepare the paste, take garlic, green chilies, cumin seeds, and carom seeds in a mixer jar and grind them to a paste.
To knead the puri dough:Now in a large mixing bowl, add wheat flour, sorghum flour, gram flour, and salt. Mix everything well.Heat the oil taken for shortening until it's very hot, and pour it over the flour mixture. First mix using a spoon, then rub it into the flour with your hands thoroughly.Now add the prepared paste, turmeric, white sesame seeds, chopped coriander, and dried fenugreek leaves. Mix well and knead into a stiff dough by adding a little water at a time.After kneading, apply a little oil on the dough and cover it for 10 minutes.
While rolling the puris:Roll one large roti (flatbread) and cut puris using a glass or tumbler, or roll small individual puris and keep ready for frying.
Frying the puris:Heat oil on medium flame. Once the oil is hot, add a few puris at a time (as many as the pan can hold). After adding, reduce the flame to medium and fry the puris well on both sides until crisp and golden.

How to make tikhat mitachya purya | Ashadh Special Tikhat purya Recipe | How to make Ashadh special kapanya dhapate recipe
For the paste:To prepare the paste, take garlic, green chilies, cumin seeds, and carom seeds in a mixer jar and grind them to a paste.
To knead the puri dough:Now in a large mixing bowl, add wheat flour, sorghum flour, gram flour, and salt. Mix everything well.Heat the oil taken for shortening until it's very hot, and pour it over the flour mixture. First mix using a spoon, then rub it into the flour with your hands thoroughly.Now add the prepared paste, turmeric, white sesame seeds, chopped coriander, and dried fenugreek leaves. Mix well and knead into a stiff dough by adding a little water at a time.After kneading, apply a little oil on the dough and cover it for 10 minutes.
While rolling the puris:Roll one large roti (flatbread) and cut puris using a glass or tumbler, or roll small individual puris and keep ready for frying.
Frying the puris:Heat oil on medium flame. Once the oil is hot, add a few puris at a time (as many as the pan can hold). After adding, reduce the flame to medium and fry the puris well on both sides until crisp and golden.
Note:These puris are traditionally made during the month of Ashadha and served with raw mango pieces. Once cooled, they can be stored in an airtight container and will stay fresh for up to a month. They are a great option for travel or picnics.

Is episode mein Ram Kapoor yaad karte hain apne health struggles ‚Äî jab unka wazan 140 kg tha aur roz khane se pehle 3 baar insulin lena padta tha. Doctor ne kaha tha, "Change or face a diabetic stroke."

Ram ne decide kiya: "Mujhe sirf fit nahi, apna best version banna hai." Aaj woh kehte hain: "Six-pack abs tak rukne wala nahi hoon!"

Unhone openly baat ki Ozempic medication, physiotherapy, aur apni 9-month recovery journey ke baare mein ‚Äî sab kuch ek honest, inspiring tone mein.

Mona Singh share karti hain kaise ek shoulder injury ne unhe yoga ki taraf laaya ‚Äî aur kaise usne unki life change kar di.
Unhone apna simple aur natural diet plan bhi bataya ‚Äî "Ladies ke liye yeh sabse safe option hai."

Dono ne discuss kiya apna upcoming show "Mistry" ‚Äî ek Indian detective drama inspired by Monk ‚Äî jisme pehli baar Ram aur Mona ek saath screen share kar rahe hain.

Ek episode full of transformation, laughter, and honest reflections ‚Äî sirf @bhartitv  Podcast par. üéôÔ∏èüî•

#YeRishtaKyaKehelataHai #YRKKH #SaasBahuAurSaazish #SBS #abhira #armaan 

*Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai* is a long-running Indian television drama that explores family relationships, love, and societal dynamics through its evolving storylines. The show, which began with Akshara and Naitik's journey, has progressed through generations, maintaining its core theme of familial bonds. In the current track, the focus has shifted to a new generation, highlighting the lives of Abhira (the union of Abhimanyu and Akshara's legacy), Armaan, and Ruhi. These characters navigate their relationships, ambitions, and the challenges of their lineage while upholding the values of the Goenka and Birla families. The blend of drama, emotions, and cultural nuances continues to resonate with viewers, ensuring its enduring popularity.

In this explosively funny finale, Prashann Kumar interviews the most iconic character of Indian households ‚Äî the middle-class desi father. From love marriage vs arranged marriage, therapy jokes, toxic parenting, and Sonam-Raja-style honeymoon murder fears, to Parents Teacher Meetings slaps, privacy invasion, Instagram spying, and beating kids for spelling ‚Äúchummi‚Äù wrong, this episode brutally exposes what it‚Äôs like growing up with a ‚Äútraditional Indian dad.‚Äù

Whether you‚Äôre a college student, a working professional, a new-age parent, or just someone in therapy because of one ‚Äì you‚Äôll relate, and laugh out loud.

Danish Taimoor breathes life into Sher Zaman, a man raised with command in his veins‚Äîfierce, proud, and built to lead.
Sarah Khan shines as Fajar, a gentle heart swept into the storm of a family feud, trying to hold on to love and light in a world clouded by old grudges.

Their paths were never meant to cross. But love‚Ä¶ had other plans.

Sher is a gripping Pakistani drama packed with raw emotions, intense rivalries, and deep-rooted traditions.

snippet.title: The Running Man | Official Trailer (2025 Movie) - Edgar Wright, Glen Powell
snippet.description:
Millions Hunt. One Runs. Everyone Watches. Watch the Official Trailer for The #RunningManMovie ‚Äì Only in theatres November 7

‚ÄãIn a near-future society, The Running Man is the top-rated show on television‚Äîa deadly competition where contestants, known as Runners, must survive 30 days while being hunted by professional assassins, with every move broadcast to a bloodthirsty public and each day bringing a greater cash reward. Desperate to save his sick daughter, working-class Ben Richards (Glen Powell) is convinced by the show‚Äôs charming but ruthless producer, Dan Killian (Josh Brolin), to enter the game as a last resort. But Ben‚Äôs defiance, instincts, and grit turn him into an unexpected fan favorite‚Äîand a threat to the entire system. As ratings skyrocket, so does the danger, and Ben must outwit not just the Hunters, but a nation addicted to watching him fall.
